{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d929a042-47ab-4820-9dd9-419f7988271a","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing a .NET crash dump. Unfortunately, I don't have a specialized skill for **analyzing** dumps (only for collecting them), but here's how you can investigate:\n\n**Recommended tools:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** — cross-platform, easiest for managed .NET crashes\n2. **WinDbg** (Windows) — with SOS extension for deep native + managed analysis\n3. **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n\n**Key commands in `dotnet-dump analyze`:**\n\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `printexception` / `pe` | Show the last exception |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n| `clrstack` | Show managed call stack |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM) |\n| `eestack` | All threads' stacks |\n\n**Quick start:**\n```bash\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n# Then inside the REPL:\n> pe -nested      # print exception chain\n> threads         # find faulting thread\n> setthread <id>  # switch to it\n> clrstack        # see what it was doing\n```\n\nWould you like help with:\n- Installing `dotnet-dump` and running these commands?\n- Interpreting specific output you're seeing?\n- A particular error type (OOM, stack overflow, access violation, deadlock)?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a6140ddc-a5bb-4cbf-bc2e-d81b1d30f8e0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me look at the available skills to see if any of them are relevant.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstones\n\n\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple crash logs\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing .dmp files. Since the `dump-collect` skill explicitly excludes dump analysis, I'll need to help the user directly by guiding them through the analysis process using tools like `dotnet-dump analyze`, WinDbg, or lldb depending on their platform.","outputTokens":606,"requestId":"501D:1FBC5F:288833:32B3E1:69F55588"},"id":"1bdaadc2-3320-48a5-8bfd-0d646e447e6a","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:38:31.535Z","parentId":"932678ac-a644-4f5a-8653-aa5344e668ab"}
